<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870526-0013 </DOCNO><HL> Securities-Industry CurbsOn Boesky Put Into Effect</HL><DD> 05/26/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)SECURITIES INDUSTRY (SCR)SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION (SEC) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Securities and Exchange Commission put into effect its order barring insider-trading figure Ivan F. Boesky from the securities industry.    The commission had issued the ban last Nov. 14, but granted Mr. Boesky a temporary stay to give him time to sell his securities businesses. The agency said Friday that Mr. Boesky has completed selling those businesses, and ordered the ban formally imposed. The action took effect last Wednesday.    The order bars Mr. Boesky from association with any broker, dealer, investment adviser, investment company or municipal-securities dealer. </TEXT></DOC>